      "comment": "DESPICABLE MARGO (1) had been racing in honest fashion recording two placings in a row before finishing fourth (17.78) at this track latest. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Has ability and is a key runner. PARIS PARTY (6) was game in defeat at the latest run, finishing second and beaten 0.8 lengths (18.37) behind Chrisy's Wish at Richmond. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Expecting another good run. QUEEN CARAMEL (7) goes very well at the distance with two wins and a placing from six starts. Below best last time at Richmond (18.69) in a Grade 5, finishing a 5.5 lengths sixth. Can feature in the finish. VERGLAS (3) gets a chance to improve on an unplaced run at her latest outing at this circuit.",
